Ball Corp. Doubles Serbia Output With New EU35 Million Can Line

-- B y   G o r d a n a   F i l i p o v i c
-- 
2011-09-16T13:13:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/ball-corp-doubles-serbia-output-with-new-eu35-million-can-line.html
Ball Packaging  Europe , part of  Ball
Corp. (BLL) , added a new can-making line to its existing facility in
Belgrade today, doubling its output in the Balkan country
designed for export markets, it said in an e-mail.  The company, which invested 35 million euros ($48 million)
in the new unit that will lift total output in Serbia to 1.5
billion cans from 750 million, will add 50 jobs and sell cans to
“markets in the region and the European Union,” the company
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gordana Filipovic in Belgrade at 
 gfilipovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
